HEADWORD: Decade
<hw>Dec"ade</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧cade</ets>, L. <ets>decas</ets>, <ets>-adis</ets>, fr. Gr.
<?/, fr. <grk>de`ka</grk> ten. See <er>Ten</er>.]</ety> <def>A group or
division of ten; esp., a period of ten years; a decennium; <as>as, a
<ex>decade</ex> of years or days; a <ex>decade</ex> of soldiers; the
second <ex>decade</ex> of Livy.</as></def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>decad</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>During this notable <qex>decade</qex> of years.</q>
<rj><qau>Gladstone.</qau></rj></p>

